    <section class="section-paragraph section-faqs">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Landing Page FAQs</h2>
            <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage" class="row">
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse1">
                            {# Q1 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">What is a landing page?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse1" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>A landing page is a webpage created specifically for a digital marketing campaign. A tailored landing page is designed to guide your visitors to a single goal.</p>
                                <p>Want your web visitors to become paying customers? You need a seamless transition from the ad to the website. If your ad promises a specific benefit but then "lands" on a generic page, you'll end up losing visitors.</p>
                                <p>A landing page is tailored to the people clicking on your ads. It talks specifically to their needs and guides them to convert.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse2">
                            {# Q2 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">Do I need a landing page?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse2" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Do you want customers? A landing page is designed with a single goal in mind: To get the people who clicked on your ad to become paying customers.</p>
                                <p>Your landing page is your best foot forward to get people to sign up or buy something. Most pages on your website cover a lot of ground, to explain your products and services. They may have many links or Call-to-Actions (CTAs) to click on.</p>
                                <p>A landing page is streamlined and tailored to the people clicking on your ads. It's designed entirely around boosting the conversion rates of your ad campaigns.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse3">
                            {# Q3 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">What makes a good landing page?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse3" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>The best landing pages are clear to understand and beautiful to interact with. Your landing page should follow best-practice design principles to help people convert.</p>
                                <p>Use features that people can't help but pay attention to. Have faces, gentle movement and high-resolution images. Get straight to the point. Your web visitors will only hang around as long as it benefits them.</p>
                                <p>Your ad landing page should look like something your customers want to see! Optimise your landing page to boost the conversion rate and ROI of your marketing campaigns.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse4">
                            {# Q4 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">Is the landing page and home page the same?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse4" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Landing pages and home pages are built for different users, and different purposes. Focus your landing pages on driving the maximum ROI from your digital marketing campaigns.</p>
                                <p>A home page is the gateway to explore your services. It's a general overview. Meanwhile, the ad landing page is where people "land" after clicking on an ad. They have focussed messaging to get people to convert. They're designed for the sale.</p>
                                <p>A high-converting landing page is a tailored experience for your web visitors. Your digital marketing depends on a landing page design that can compel customers to convert.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse5">
                            {# Q6 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">What is an e-commerce landing page?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse5" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>An e-commerce landing page is a webpage created for an e-commerce digital marketing campaign. It's designed to drive home the sale and get your customer buying.</p>
                                <p>Many of the best practices of landing page design have to be tailored for e-commerce campaigns. The landing page has to specifically show the products the person was promised in the ad. The page needs to be flexible for people who want to browse, but always focus on the sale.</p>
                                <p>It's not a product page! The success of your e-commerce campaign hinges on having landing page designs that convert.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
                    <div itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question" class="card">
                        <div class="card-header collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse6">
                            {# Q6 #}
                            <h3 itemprop="name">How do you test a landing page?</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" id="collapse6" class="collapse">
                            <div itemprop="text" class="card-body">
                                <p>Testing is key to make your landing page as effective as possible at driving sales. The better your landing page, the more sales it'll drive. Testing is how you get there.</p>
                                <p>Landing page tests are experiments to find out which aspects of the landing page design drive conversion. You need data analysis experts to work out what is the best landing page design to drive the most sales for you.</p>
                                <p>If you can boost the conversion rate of your landing page, you can make more money without spending. Landing page tests can boost conversion rates to maximise your ROI.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

